Meta and VR as Console
----------------------

Alex Cranz had an opinion piece on The Verge ( https://www.theverge.com/202=
3/3/4/23623081/meta-quest-3-ps3-xbox-one-video-games-yikes ) complaining th=
at Meta wasn=E2=80=99t treating the Quest like the console that he claims i=
t is:

Meta changed its name because it wanted you to forever associate it with th=
e nascent metaverse. The hardware it produces is meant to be our window int=
o that metaverse. When you pick up a Meta Quest 2 headset and slip it over =
your head, you=E2=80=99re meant to gasp and softly wonder at this new virtu=
al world. But I put on my Meta Quest 2 to play Beat Saber or Tetris or mayb=
e Pistol Whip. It=E2=80=99s not a terminal into the metaverse =E2=80=94 it=
=E2=80=99s a game console. And I don=E2=80=99t think Meta realizes that=E2=
=80=A6

That plan to focus on something new and different instead of the games that=
 made the console thrive is very similar to what Microsoft did when it laun=
ched the Xbox One. That device came with an IR blaster! It had a coax line =
in so you could use it as a cable box. Microsoft pitched the Xbox One as a =
home theater computer that also played games. And the gamers just went and =
bought the Playstation 4 instead.

